D.  Manuscript Editor (international, 6 person-months, 2 consultants) 

4.  Under the direct supervision of ACE, ERMF and in coordination with the relevant ERMF 
staff, the manuscript editor will: 
(i)  edit  the ADO including  
(a)  rewriting,  reorganizing,  or  shortening  the  text  to  improve  its  logical 
structure and sharpen the arguments;  
(b)  simplifying  technical  language,  eliminating  jargon,  and  introducing 
definitions  so  that  the  chapters  can  be  understood  by  an  educated 
nonspecialist;  
(c)  coordinating with the authors and economics editors to make connections 
among ideas explicit and to illustrate complex concepts;  
(d)  cutting or editing redundant passages and simplifying long, complicated 
sentences;  
(e)  smoothening or writing transitions between paragraphs and sections; and  
(f)  suggesting additional materials (e.g., boxes, tables, figures) that would 
make the publication more reader-friendly;  
(ii)  check the manuscript for consistency and accuracy including  
(a)  checking for factual errors (e.g., whether correct names of institutions and 
other entities are used; verifying major statements of fact on authoritative 
websites, where practical); and  
(b)  highlighting data inconsistencies (e.g., alerting ERMF national  staff to 
discrepancies in data among text, tables, and charts for their chapters 
and  ensuring  that  queries  are  answered;  and  ensuring  that  the 
benchmarks are referred to coherently in the publication); 
(iii)  copyedit  all  parts  of the reports  in conformity  with  ADB’s  editorial style  and 
usage;

