(iv)  smooth out the entire structure of the publications to make them readable with a 
consistent logical flow; 
(v)  ensure, to a degree possible, consistency of language style in all parts of the 
publication; 
(vi)  edit tables and figures; 
(vii)  ensure that subheads are consistent and logical; 
(viii)  check references to tables, figures, appendixes, bibliographies, and parts of the 
text; 
(ix)  edit notes to make sure that the text references are correct; 
(x)  supervise the encoding of corrections as well as incorporation of tables, charts, 
and boxes; 
(xi)  prepare the table of contents, definition of terms, and list of acronyms; 
(xii)  edit all dissemination materials including press releases, speeches, questions 
and answers, key messages, and presentation slides;  
(xiii)  liaise with the typesetter designated by ERMF to ensure that editorial marks and 
comments, as well as tables, charts, and boxes, are incorporated in the typeset 
manuscript upon submission for final printing; 
(xiv)  perform all other functions as may be assigned by ACE, ERMF; and 
(xv)  deliver the following output: edited manuscript. 

E.  Resource Persons (0.6 person-months, 6 experts) 

5.  Selected staff from resident missions will be invited as resource persons during the ADO 
writers’  workshop  to  present  and  discuss  current  country  conditions  in  preparation for the 
drafting of the ADO country chapters. 

6.  Resource persons (from both local institutions and offices of international organizations 
in the region) with knowledge of the theme chapter topics will also be engaged to act as 
discussants during the ADO theme conferences.  

F.  Desktop Publishing Specialist and Graphic Designer (national, 13 person-months, 
2 consultants) 

7.  The  consultants  must  be  skilled  in  working  with  Adobe InDesign,  Adobe  Illustrator, 
Adobe  Photoshop,  Microsoft  Word,  and  Microsoft  Excel.  The  consultants  will  typeset  and 
proofread the text, tables, charts and all graphic elements of the publication from the preliminary 
draft to the final copy and produce the high resolution PDF file before forwarding to the external 
printer (including refining its web version). In particular, the consultants will  
(i)  lay out the ADO; 
(ii)  reformat tables and charts of the ADO based on corrections received from ERMF 
staff and consultants; 
(iii)  encode corrections in the main text based on corrections received from ERMF 
staff and consultants; 
(iv)  prepare final layout of the ADO; 
(v)  encode final text and graphical corrections; 
(vi)  deliver the web-ready and pre-flighted consolidated PDF of the publication; 
(vii)  perform other related tasks as assigned by ACE, ERMF; and 
(viii)  deliver the following outputs: PDF files of the different parts of the book at certain 
points  of  the  production  process;  source  files  (InDesign  and  Illustrator) 
preliminary and final; PDF file of the manuscript for launch, printing, and web-
posting; and backup of all files submitted
